  "title": "Process Engineer (Black Utilities)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary:</strong></p><p>We are seeking a skilled <strong>Process Engineer (Black Utilities)</strong> to design, manage, and optimize power equipment systems, including chilled water, compressed air, and steam systems. The role involves system calculation, layout design, equipment selection, and technical coordination across disciplines.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>1. Responsible for the design of power equipment systems, including chilled water systems,heating hot water, compressed air systems, and steam systems;</p><p>3. Responsible for calculating the requirements of the aforementioned power systems, designing system layouts, piping systems, and selecting equipment;</p><p>4. Participate in compiling data sheets for various power system equipment and valves, and conduct technical bid evaluations;</p><p>5. Possess thorough knowledge of conventional power equipment brands, their characteristics and performance;</p><p>6. Coordinate interdisciplinary requirements and review process compliance in design documents returned by other disciplines;</p><p>7. Monitor industry developments, assist in company marketing activities and technical presentations.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>1. Bachelor's degree or higher in HVAC, Energy, Thermal Engineering, or related disciplines;</p><p>2. Minimum 5 years' experience in power or heating/cooling source system design and engineering management;</p><p>3. Proficient in CAD and other design software; comprehensive knowledge of cleanroom design standards and specifications;</p><p>4. Outgoing personality, good health, integrity, with strong time management and self-discipline;</p><p>5. Excellent communication and presentation skills, strong sense of responsibility, fluent English preferred.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p><ul><li>14 days annual leave</li><li>AWS</li><li>Phone allowance</li><li>Medical insurance</li></ul>",
